'''Anna Chancellor''' (born 27 April 1965) is a British actress.
==Family== Chancellor was born in [[Richmond, London|Richmond]], [[London]], England, the daughter of the Hon. Mary Alice Jolliffe (daughter of [[William Jolliffe, 4th Baron Hylton]]) and John Paget Chancellor. Through her mother's mother, Lady Perdita Rose Mary Asquith, Chancellor is the great-granddaughter of [[Raymond Asquith|The Hon. Raymond Aquith]] and the great-great-granddaughter of Prime Minister [[H. H. Asquith]],<ref>[http://www.thegreenmag.co.uk/Editorial.aspx?brand=GREENOnline&category=GREENProfiles&story=SPED21+Mar+2007+13%3A26%3A07%3A013&page=1572 Green - Aristocratic Anna<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and through her father, she is the great-great-granddaughter of the [[Murray Finch-Hatton, 12th Earl of Winchilsea|12th Earl of Winchilsea and Nottingham]] (a descendant of [[Thomas Cecil, 1st Earl of Exeter]] and [[William Cecil, 1st Baron Burghley]]). She is distantly related to actress [[Helena Bonham Carter]], through her mother's side. Her uncle is journalist [[Alexander Chancellor]], the father of model [[Cecilia Chancellor]], her eight-times great-aunt was author [[Jane Austen]], herself a great-niece of [[James Brydges, 1st Duke of Chandos]], and her second cousin six times removed was poet [[Lord Byron]]. She is also twice a descendant of [[Mary Boleyn]] and once of [[Richard Rich, 1st Baron Rich]] and [[John Churchill, 1st Duke of Marlborough]].{{Citation needed|date=December 2010}}
Chancellor was accepted into the [[London Academy of Music and Dramatic Art]], but in her third year she became pregnant and dropped out.{{Citation needed|date=December 2010}} Her daughter with Scots poet Jock Scott, Poppy Chancellor, was born in 1988. When their relationship ended, she then married a cameraman, Nigel Willoughby, whom she had met in 1993 while shooting a Boddington's advertisement. However, they divorced in 1998.{{Citation needed|date=December 2010}} She is now married to Redha Debbah.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2011/aug/21/anna-chancellor-interview-the-hour|title=The Observer - My life was chaotic. But it turned out OK. |publisher=guardian.co.uk |year=2011 |accessdate=2011-08-22}}</ref>
==Career== Chancellor had a prominent role in the series ''[[Kavanagh QC]]''. She is also known for her performance as "Duckface" in ''[[Four Weddings and a Funeral]]'' opposite [[Hugh Grant]]. She has also been noted for her work as Caroline Bingley in the [[Pride and Prejudice (1995 mini-series)|1995 BBC adaptation of ''Pride and Prejudice'']], and as Questular Rontok in ''[[The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (film)|The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy]]''. In 2005, she joined the cast of the popular [[BBC One]] television drama series ''[[Spooks]]'' as a new regular character, [[Juliet Shaw]]. She has also appeared in ''[[The Vice (TV series)|The Vice]]'', ''[[Jupiter Moon]]'', ''[[Karaoke (play)|Karaoke]]'', ''[[Cold Lazarus]]'', ''[[The Dreamers (film)|The Dreamers]]'', and ''[[Tipping the Velvet (TV serial)|Tipping the Velvet]]'', and has a starring role in the satirical black comedy ''[[Suburban Shootout]]''. In 2011, she took a supporting role in the thriller serial ''The Hour''.<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1778108/ ''The Hour''] at IMDb</ref>
==Charity== She is one of the Honorary Patrons of the London children's charity [[Scene & Heard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sceneandheard.org/about_whoweare.html |title=Scene & Heard - Who We Are |publisher=sceneandheard.org |year=2010 |accessdate=2010-06-19}}</ref>
